    • #Newline
  • Turing himself did not explicitly state that the Turing test could be used as a measure of intelligence#Comma or any other human quality.#Newline
    • #Newline
  • In practice#Comma the Turing test's results can easily be dominated not by the computer's intelligence#Comma but by the attitudes and skill of the questioner.#Newline
    • #Newline
  • Mainstream AI researchers argue that trying to pass the Turing Test is merely a distraction from more fruitful research.#Newline
    • #Newline
  • Turing predicted that machines would eventually be able to pass the test; in fact#Comma he estimated that by the year 2000#Comma machines with approximately 120 megabytes of memory would be able to fool thirty percent of human judges in a five-minute test.#Newline
